content.description:
This unique route will give you some confidence on high balls. While you are climbing you won't feel like you are very high, but you are.

It's a beautiful clean route with a fun mantle.

SDS at Cat in the Cradle would make for a fun variation on this route.
content.location: on the east face of the electric bobcat next to the walkable slab. Being on the right arete and move left to a slopey shelf. reach for some good holds to mantle and topout.

content.description: Begin sds just right of Cat Woman. Use slightly awkward right foot to stand to crimp. Work leftward to slopey indented feature. work your feet high and commit to slopey ledge to the left.
content.location: Just to the right of Cat Woman and to the left of the right arete.

content.description:
Begin under the prow, following the obvious crack leftward to a nice crimp. Throw left and top out up the easy slab.

Alt top out: After following the crack reach for the roof just above and mantle. A little sktechy considering the height, but super fun! Pulling over the roof = V1
content.protection: Multiple pads and a spotter recommended
content.location: Huge boulder about half way up the hill. About 20 yards south of the lion's mane.

content.description: The crux is the dedicated standing move reaching for the sloper rail at the top. Good landing though.
content.location: Begin SDS. use decent crimps and ledges to meet the interesting dip feature. get high feet and dedicate to move to slopey rail.

content.description: Begin on the high holds at the low hanging apex of the prow.  Use fairly difficult holds to a sketchy mantle then climb leftward to topout. (Direct is still asking to be sent!)
content.protection: A lot of pads for a proper landing (small boulders below will make blood come out if you fall) and a strong spotter or two.
content.location: Located on the same boulder as Electric Bobcat just to the right.

content.description:
Fun route to get to the top of Electric Bobcat. Can also be used as a down climb.

the sit start gives this climb some fun movements.
content.location: Located on the left arete on the northern side of Electric Bobcat boulder.

climbs.name: Cat Bus AKA ねこのバス (Neko no basu)

content.description: This is a fun warmup problem that ends with a nice view of green pastures during late winter early spring months. Reminiscent of the beautiful imagined worlds by the great Hayao Miyazaki. Travel with Totoro to meet the Catbus at the top of this fun route.
content.location: Take the right arete up to the Catbus stop.

content.description: Direct start to Electric Bob Cat
